@node Readability exceptions
@section Readability exceptions

@vindex eww-extras-readable-exceptions
@vindex eww-extras-readable-exceptions-file
The user option @code{eww-extras-readable-exceptions} holds a list of URL
patterns (strings treated as regular expressions) for which
@code{eww-readable} should not be automatically applied.  The default value
is an empty list.  This variable is populated at load time from the file
specified by @code{eww-extras-readable-exceptions-file} and updated whenever
you add a new exception via
@code{eww-extras-add-domain-to-readable-exceptions}
(@ref{Adding readability exceptions}).

The user option @code{eww-extras-readable-exceptions-file} specifies the
path to the file containing readability exception patterns, one per
line.  The default value is @samp{etc/eww-readable-exceptions.txt} within
the Emacs configuration directory (via @code{paths-dir-dotemacs}).  You would
change this if you want to store the exceptions file elsewhere.

@node Chrome data directory
@section Chrome data directory

@vindex eww-extras-chrome-data-dir
The user option @code{eww-extras-chrome-data-dir} specifies the path to the
main Google Chrome profile directory.  The default value is
@samp{~/Library/Application Support/Google/Chrome/}.  This directory is used
as the source when creating profile copies for headless Chrome sessions
(@ref{Chrome data management}).  You should only change this if Chrome stores
its data in a non-standard location.

