@node Readability management
@section Readability management

@findex eww-extras-readable-autoview
@findex eww-extras-set-readable-exceptions-from-file
The function @code{eww-extras-readable-autoview} is added to
@code{eww-after-render-hook}.  It automatically calls @code{eww-readable} unless
the current URL matches a pattern in @code{eww-extras-readable-exceptions} or
the page has no source content to process.

The function @code{eww-extras-set-readable-exceptions-from-file} reads the
exception patterns from @code{eww-extras-readable-exceptions-file} and
populates the @code{eww-extras-readable-exceptions} variable.  It is called
automatically at load time and after adding a new exception.

@node YouTube handling
@section YouTube handling

@findex eww-extras-browse-youtube
The function @code{eww-extras-browse-youtube} is designed as a handler for
YouTube URLs (e.g., in @code{browse-url-handlers}).  When called with a
YouTube URL, it kills the current EWW buffer, ensures the external
video player is running (defaulting to @samp{mpv}), and fetches the video
transcript using @code{elfeed-tube-fetch}.  This provides a workflow where
you read the transcript in Emacs while watching the video in an external
player.

@node File generation internals
@section File generation internals

@findex eww-extras-url-to-file
@findex eww-extras-url-to-file-make-command
@findex eww-extras-url-to-file-sentinel
@findex eww-extras-run-callback
The function @code{eww-extras-url-to-file} is the core logic shared by
@code{eww-extras-url-to-pdf} and @code{eww-extras-url-to-html}.  It determines
the URL and output file name from context, constructs and starts the
headless Chrome process, and sets up the process sentinel.

The function @code{eww-extras-url-to-file-make-command} builds the shell
command for headless Chrome, including GPU disabling flags and a
15-second timeout.

The function @code{eww-extras-url-to-file-sentinel} creates a process
sentinel that checks the exit status.  It runs the callback on success,
or if the file was created despite a non-zero exit status (which can
happen with certain Chrome warnings).

The function @code{eww-extras-run-callback} safely executes the optional
callback function with the output file and Bib@TeX{} key as arguments.

